Mod is designed to use a seperate animation shape to work with a static shape to get it to work properly - animation shape can contain multiple animations, limited to 2 per part and needs to be referenced in the JSON attributesByType

Required: One entry per texture reference used in the shape
AttributeRenderingLibrary will override these with the chosen material variant	
"frame": "game:block/wood/planks/oak1", // fallback; AttributeRenderingLibrary will override with {wood}
"glass": "game:block/glass/leaded", // fallback for {glass}
"putty": "game:block/wood/debarked/oak"

"animations":
 

"name": "Open",
"code": "open", used in animOpen, can be called anything
"quantityframes": 30,
"onActivityStopped": "EaseOut",
"onAnimationEnd": "Hold", Required for the animated part to stay visible
 

"name": "Closed",
"code": "closed", used in animClosed, can be called anything
"quantityframes": 30,
"onActivityStopped": "EaseOut",
"onAnimationEnd": "Hold", Required for the animated part to stay visible
